  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "If my boyfriend chooses to spend my birthday with someone else is that a bad sign?",
  "response": "If your boyfriend chooses to spend your birthday with someone else instead of you, it could indicate a few things, and it\u2019s worth reflecting on the situation and having an open conversation with him. Here are some possible interpretations:\n\n1. **Lack of Prioritization**: Birthdays are special occasions, and if your boyfriend chose to spend it with someone else without a valid reason, it might suggest he\u2019s not prioritizing your relationship or your feelings at the moment.\n\n2. **Miscommunication or Oversight**: It\u2019s possible that he didn\u2019t realize how important this was to you or that there was a misunderstanding about plans. Some people don\u2019t place as much significance on birthdays as others.\n\n3. **Personal Circumstances**: There might be a legitimate reason he chose to be with someone else, such as a close friend or family member going through a hard time. It\u2019s worth considering the context.\n\n4. **Compatibility Issues**: This could highlight a difference in values or expectations in your relationship. For example, if birthdays are important to you but not to him, it might be a sign to discuss how you both approach special occasions.\n\n### What to Do:\n- **Communicate Your Feelings**: Let him know how his decision made you feel without being confrontational. For example, \u201cI felt hurt that we didn\u2019t spend my birthday together because it\u2019s an important day for me.\u201d\n- **Understand His Perspective**: Ask him why he made that choice and listen to his reasoning. This will help you understand his intentions.\n- **Set Expectations**: Discuss how you\u2019d like to handle future special occasions to ensure you\u2019re both on the same page.\n\nUltimately, whether this is a \u201cbad sign\u201d depends on the context, his response, and how he treats you overall in the relationship. If this is part of a pattern of neglect or disregard for your feelings, it\u2019s worth evaluating the relationship more seriously. If it\u2019s an isolated incident and he\u2019s apologetic, it could be an opportunity to grow and improve your communication.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
